searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest","doc":"Structured request compiled from semantic intent after manifest validation.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest.new/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ActionRequest.html#new/1"},{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence","doc":"Fence view projected from a lease.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.from_lease/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.html#from_lease/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.newer_than?/2","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Fence.html#newer_than?/2"},{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease","doc":"Lease contract for one semantic-session owner.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.expired?/2","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.html#expired?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.new/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.Lease.html#new/1"},{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication","doc":"Durable reply publication state for semantic output.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.phase/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#t:phase/0"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.state/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#t:state/0"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.new/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.valid_phase?/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#valid_phase?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.valid_state?/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ReplyPublication.html#valid_state?/1"},{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact","doc":"Durable lower-runtime fact consumed by the semantic layer.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.kind/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html#t:kind/0"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.kinds/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html#kinds/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.new/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.wake_key/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.RuntimeFact.html#wake_key/1"},{"type":"module","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot","doc":"Durable snapshot of the tool manifest presented to a model turn.","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.route_metadata/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html#t:route_metadata/0"},{"type":"type","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.t/0","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.new/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.route_names/1","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html#route_names/1"},{"type":"function","title":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.selection_valid?/2","doc":"","ref":"OuterBrain.Contracts.ToolManifestSnapshot.html#selection_valid?/2"},{"type":"extras","title":"README","doc":"# OuterBrain\n\nOuterBrain is the semantic-runtime workspace above Citadel.\n\nIt owns semantic journals, tool-manifest snapshots, prompt and strategy shaping,\nsemantic quality checkpoints, live session fencing, and restart-safe reply\npublication.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Scope - README","doc":"- raw input normalization\n- semantic state and journaling\n- context assembly\n- prompt and strategy shaping\n- structured action-request synthesis\n- provisional and final reply publication\n- restart-safe downstream follow-up","ref":"readme.html#scope"},{"type":"extras","title":"Status - README","doc":"Active workspace buildout. The repo uses a non-umbrella workspace layout with\ncore packages, bridges, a host surface, and proving examples.","ref":"readme.html#status"},{"type":"extras","title":"Development - README","doc":"The project targets Elixir `~> 1.19` and Erlang/OTP `28`. The pinned toolchain\nlives in `.tool-versions`.\n\n```bash\nmix deps.get\nmix ci\n```\n\nThe welded `outer_brain_contracts` artifact is tracked through the prepared\nbundle flow:\n\n```bash\nmix release.prepare\nmix release.track\nmix release.archive\n```\n\n`mix release.track` updates the orphan-backed\n`projection/outer_brain_contracts` branch so downstream repos can pin a real\ngenerated-source ref before any formal release boundary exists.","ref":"readme.html#development"},{"type":"extras","title":"Documentation - README","doc":"- `docs/overview.md`\n- `docs/layout.md`\n- `docs/runtime_model.md`\n- `docs/integration_surface.md`\n- `CHANGELOG.md`\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License.\n(c) 2026 nshkrdotcom. See `LICENSE`.","ref":"readme.html#documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Integration Surface","doc":"# Integration Surface\n\nThis repository integrates with:\n\n- Citadel for structured policy decisions\n- `jido_domain` for typed route input that becomes a durable manifest snapshot\n- `jido_integration` for durable lower runtime facts and restart authority below\n  the semantic layer\n- `ground_plane` projection helpers through a bridge seam\n- host shells and APIs through the `host_surface` app\n\nThe bridge packages in this workspace keep those seams explicit and replayable.\n\nThe welded `outer_brain_contracts` artifact is tracked through the prepared\nbundle flow:\n\n```bash\nmix release.prepare\nmix release.track\nmix release.archive\n```\n\n`mix release.track` updates the orphan-backed\n`projection/outer_brain_contracts` branch so downstream repos can pin a real\ngenerated-source ref before any formal release boundary exists.","ref":"integration_surface.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Current Lowering Path - Integration Surface","doc":"The semantic lowering path is now:\n\n- turn input is selected onto a typed route by `OuterBrain.Core.TurnSelector`\n- route metadata is compiled into a stable tool and route manifest snapshot by\n  `OuterBrain.Bridges.ManifestCompiler`\n- semantic submission into the typed domain layer is owned by\n  `OuterBrain.Bridges.DomainSubmission`\n- the lower typed route then flows through `jido_domain`, the public\n  `Citadel.HostIngress` seam, and the real `jido_integration` ingress path\n\nThis keeps `outer_brain` responsible for semantic selection and packaging, not\nfor durable lower-truth ownership.","ref":"integration_surface.html#current-lowering-path"},{"type":"extras","title":"Workspace Layout","doc":"# Workspace Layout\n\nThe repo is a non-umbrella workspace root.\n\nKey groups:\n\n- `core/outer_brain_contracts`\n- `core/outer_brain_journal`\n- `core/outer_brain_core`\n- `core/outer_brain_prompting`\n- `core/outer_brain_quality`\n- `core/outer_brain_runtime`\n- `core/outer_brain_restart_authority`\n- `bridges/*`\n- `apps/host_surface`\n- `examples/*`\n\nThis split keeps the semantic runtime explainable without turning the root repo\ninto one large opaque application.","ref":"layout.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Overview","doc":"# Overview\n\nOuterBrain is the semantic-runtime workspace that sits above Citadel and below\nhost surfaces.\n\nIt owns the language-facing work that should not live in the deterministic\npolicy kernel:\n\n- raw ingress journaling\n- semantic-frame reduction\n- context-pack construction\n- tool-manifest snapshots compiled from typed routes\n- quality checkpoints\n- provisional and final reply publication\n- restart-safe semantic recovery\n\nThe repo is intentionally split into contracts, journal, prompting, quality,\nruntime, restart authority, bridges, and proving examples so semantic authority,\npolicy authority, and lower durable execution truth stay separated.","ref":"overview.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Runtime Model","doc":"# Runtime Model\n\nOuterBrain owns the durable semantic loop above Citadel.\n\nThe runtime loop is:\n\n1. capture a raw turn in the semantic journal\n2. acquire the semantic-session fence for the current epoch\n3. build a context pack and strategy profile\n4. validate model-selected work against the stored manifest snapshot\n5. compile an action request or clarification\n6. publish provisional or final user-facing state\n7. normalize lower facts into a single wake path\n8. recover or reconcile from durable evidence after restart\n\nCitadel remains the policy kernel beneath this layer, and `jido_integration`\nremains the durable lower execution owner.","ref":"runtime_model.html"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}